@node envGet  "environment/Get Env"

   @{u}Get Env...@{uu}  (shortcut: 'G',  menu: right Amiga 'G')

    This is a requester of the contents of a selected environment.
    The value is shown in the string gadget. A string gadget can only
    show ASCI Charaters. Env can`t edit binary files - of you load binary data
    into this gadget non charaters will be filtered out. If you press @{"Save" link envgets }
    or @{"Use" link envgetu } the file will be over written with filtered data, but if you press
    @{"Cancel" link envgets} no file will be touched.

                                @{u}To leave this window use:@{uu}
    · right Amiga 'S'
    same as @{"Save" link envgets}. Replace the contents of the selected environment with the contents
    of the string gadget. Make this environment ready to use, until its deleted.

    · right Amiga 'U'
    same as @{"Use" link envgetu}. Replace the contents of the selected environment with the contents
    of the string gadget. Make this environment ready to use, but only @{b}volatile@{ub}.

    · right Amiga 'C'
    same as @{"Cancel" link envgetc } or Esc-Key

    · Esc-Key
    cancel you new contents - don`t touch any files (same as @{"Cancel" link envgetc } )

@endnode
@Node   envgets "environment/GetWin Save",

      Save          (shortcut: 'S',  menu: right Amiga 'S')

        Saves the file to "ENV:" AND also to "ENVARC:".
@endnode
@Node   envgetu "environment/GetWin User"

      Use           (shortcut: 'U',  menu: right Amiga 'U')

        "Use" saves the file only to "ENV:". normally "ENV:" is in your
        RAM Disk, so that it will be lost if you reset or switch off
        your computer.
@endnode
@Node   envgetc "environment/GetWin Cancel"

      Cancel        (shortcut: 'C',  menu: right Amiga 'C')

        "Cancel" cancels creating a new environment. Clicking on the
        gadget "Cancel" or the system's Close-Window-Gadget or pressing
        ESC or just "C" will do the same.
@endnode
